ld be package-private instead. That seems like a good point to check because it might help with encapsulation. It's important to make sure the configuration is appropriately secure while still being functional. I'll need to evaluate if having that visibility change would affect usage or accessibility in any way. Getting it right will ensure better organization of the code, which is always a positive!\"},{\"type\":\"summary_text\",\"text\":\"**Evaluating testing setup**\\n\\nI'm considering how these top-level test classes only test the public aspects, which is fine. I need to think about the default Checkstyle settings and whether it's okay to avoid wildcard imports. It seems like there's no need for multiple new files, and I should mention that I haven't run things as per instructions. Maybe I could also check for untracked files using git diff --stat and find them.\"}]}"}, {"type": "text", "text": "Implemented focused coverage for `org.springframework.boot.BeanDefinitionLoader`.\n\nAdded:\n\n- `tests/src/org.springframework.boot/spring-boot/4.0.2/src/test/java/org_springframework_boot/spring_boot/BeanDefinitionLoaderTest.java`\n  - Uses `SpringApplication` with a package-name source string.\n  - Exercises the package-loading path that reaches `BeanDefinitionLoader.findPackage(...)`.\n\n- `tests/src/org.springframework.boot/spring-boot/4.0.2/src/test/java/org_springframework_boot/spring_boot/beandefinitionloaderfixture/PackageLoadedConfiguration.java`\n  - Fixture configuration discovered from the package source.\n  - Provides a bean asserted by the test.\n\nPer instruction, I did not compile or run the tests locally.", "textSignature": "{\"v\":1,\"id\":\"msg_09bbfa71891ce904016a251dd3a7848196a24372536319dd6c\",\"phase\":\"final_answer\"}"}], "api": "openai-responses", "provider": "OCA", "model": "gpt-5.5", "usage": {"input": 337, "output": 731, "cacheRead": 29696, "cacheWrite": 0, "totalTokens": 30764, "cost": {"input": 0, "output": 0, "cacheRead": 0, "cacheWrite"