runner includes those during the build, the package would be defined.\\n\\nTo prevent conflicts, I should avoid creating a test class in that package if it's already defined.\"},{\"type\":\"summary_text\",\"text\":\"**Exploring test detection and package loading**\\n\\nI'm considering how the test detector scans all classes to identify tests. It might involve scanning bytecode without actually loading classes. If the native image includes and defines packages for all build-time classes, I wonder if I can use an existing library package that isn't loaded but contains class resources in a JAR. It's possible that `BeanDefinitionLoader's` classloader could help find defined packages for loaded Spring Boot classes in `org.springframework.boot`, but maybe some subpackages haven't been loaded yet.\"}]}"}, {"type": "toolCall", "id": "call_vuuPuKBC71R4ltsnqzQkUeye|fc_09bbfa71891ce904016a251ec2a7d4819680272998de9cf6bd", "name": "bash", "arguments": {"command": "find /home/jovan/Work/graalvm-reachability-metadata/forge/local_repositories/source_context/org.springframework.boot/spring-boot/4.0.2/main/extracted/org/springframework/boot -type f -name '*.java' | sed 's#.*/extracted/##;s#/[^/]*$##;s#/#.#g' | sort -u | head -100", "timeout": 10}, "partialJson": "{\"command\":\"find /home/jovan/Work/graalvm-reachability-metadata/forge/local_repositories/source_context/org.springframework.boot/spring-boot/4.0.2/main/extracted/org/springframework/boot -type f -name '*.java' | sed 's#.*/extracted/##;s#/[^/]*$##;s#/#.#g' | sort -u | head -100\",\"timeout\":10}"}], "api": "openai-responses", "provider": "OCA", "model": "gpt-5.5", "usage": {"input": 3206, "output": 810, "cacheRead": 31232, "cacheWrite": 0, "totalTokens": 35248, "cost": {"input": 0, "output": 0, "cacheRead": 0, "cacheWrite": 0, "total": 0}}, "stopReason": "toolUse", "timestamp": 1780817579522, "responseId": "resp_09bbfa71891ce904016a251eac90208196879439192b9900fc"}}
