[assistant] 
[assistant] Changes made:
[assistant] 
[assistant] - Restored a real fixture class:
[assistant]   - `tests/src/org.springframework.boot/spring-boot/4.0.2/src/test/java/org_springframework_boot/spring_boot/beandefinitionloaderfixture/PackageLoadedConfiguration.java`
[assistant] 
[assistant] - Removed the ineffective `package-info.java`.
[assistant] 
[assistant] - Updated the test assertion to refresh the context and verify the fixture bean:
[assistant]   - `packageLoadedMarker == "package loaded"`
[assistant] 
[assistant] The test still avoids directly referencing the fixture class, so the fixture package should remain undefined until `BeanDefinitionLoader.findPackage(...)` discovers a `.class` resource and reaches the target `Class.forName(...)` call site.
