[recv] {"type": "message_end", "message": {"role": "assistant", "content": [{"type": "thinking", "thinking": "**Evaluating test coverage**\n\nI'm considering whether the current test run coverage is complete. We're advised against running tests, but maybe we can run a tool like javap. Since there are no tests, I'm pondering why the package might be defined. In Java, a package gets defined when a class is loaded. PackageLoadedConfiguration isn't in the test source, but perhaps the Spring scanner loads it afterward. During test discovery, JUnit scans all classes, but I wonder if Gradle's scan behavior affects this. It's all a bit tricky!\n\n**Considering package definitions**\n\nI need to find a way around the short-circuiting of getDefinedPackage by using a separate package, even if all test classes are included. If all classes in the image define packages, then any included class also defines a package, but that might not be true for the JVM. The report showing \"newly covered none\" suggests there might not even be a JVM coverage call. I wonder if our package source is loaded as a resource before findPackage. If the source path maps correctly, it should load, but this string has dots that complicate things.\n\n**Considering testing access**\n\nI’m thinking about using MethodHandles or reflection to instantiate package-private elements, but that’s not allowed. I wonder if I could put the test in the `org.springframework.boot` package to access them. The developer advised keeping tests outside of library packages, so that’s a no-go. Maybe the current test source root with underscores could be included in the user-code filter. It seems like dynamic-access coverage only tracks things within the library, though.\n\n**Evaluating JVM and metadata creation**\n\nI'm considering the situation with `org.springframework.boot.ssl.pem`. It seems like if there are no static references, the JVM runs the `Class.forName` method, which could lead to the creation of metadata externally for the native test build. I'm also contemplating the role of the TCK workflow and whether it triggers a native test build with metadata sourced from test resources and repository data, rather than relying on anything generated by the agent. There's quite a bit to unpack here!", "thinkingSignature": "{\"id\":\"rs_09bbfa71891ce904016a252070e0c481968775845d7c6fe835\",\"type\":\"reasoning\",\"content\":[],\"encrypted_content\":\"gAAAAABqJSC_D3Mya-oeR0grH7rN6IsgKaeUS77NJkmQGKiHvUGC2yD4YMXOqm_0Xwr1v0AELUFbmkM4MflMIrHVwgUdjJk3nMbxhIMDUUc100BmkZq35nJ43QUMYsmACxaJrU6fMeyWOldGYyC92pgslOSEoS_1Ll6qmeYUjUNnibPAMN7J_UliVcC7j8brsit8Y04fYcYUZyDc9NFnTKTxt3yqk9yKJ9o0dTxBlPflAkAfgjXMxr_pXexMMqJYp6eva1MEYbOVMtfyYMd4KTRG51OE_SHOuYRN7vLk6y9kOzpnW6j17oJ-gIPVhO0ff0jb6cFMNzxSfM5LMpzWX7YJxMGO4JRocqXnyUqeISmITI32ZQH_g-2FdIqVwbmwigueycBPz36w_vbOaoyB4-G46jQl8DfaMxFk4cUMUlfP5pC7gSmGh6i6jNBHs2vVFT3pSTl7zgh7WzdNZP6ixLAbuM68a7MNaytbEPA6InPyc4YEjsqb9JPj0fkuxYQquWy08R2nEojmv7vhuq5igH8i53a2vuFc2zzJR9065iC_7BVaRQqq99V_XYuPglpzWMQRd4QeWbUY7wllpubhNabK4JV_JWNdbBbzsvSvrZbcYvwvcmZntPUMkWigk2bvqJeAOiH7uSQI5Y1enJI8ts3m-WZ2oZ7V280qkMxU8xF0af_yC-hQHuDgpmzo_9z6Q4Smg3mJKubYFe-aEdgvcuhwMCjcyIPBYz691zByMEqWu7l9657iHk0LXOH5PYFC5pO-TUD3gexbTyv7XSmZ36QV27rw1y_sOYQazVeWgqWpNic5vy2hkY4QVmmmc7e0gZj0-lTTKMSloq1BZ83hUSQwewYoGc1gn9dQD_gFFYNfSlpoaWveuHEFwsJzhEKDY9xCycjVCVHwUmFD_Om67rN-qFutyrKm4Z3uCcxoc2oCYNe81tNgSfb5vC9Qh0ASbMtZ2WDN-krh6gooedxajl5PjUdLylTpu6h8whjTzyAALubXrCjN0A4zwHfXvG6b5wKjkZGmqHFhSVjjB7Q9BzHkAUfXiSJgI5pfWOfZtNOpX1c8ZfsUjgmYDWWQ1Dx0ygU3oRcGbaoxN_5jYT8unNwXnZKQkVEZ5Oa_Y_FEaDvPMzJ57zKgfV-LSn8dS31DsLMvPD1lhGz-FSxd4m2rtYtyuLAi3f3xdUDuhIWRziaAaPNLVGXWHKQ2ohbXYPFNT9gc1M0IlyClCUN2H676xgtl5ZiO6by7Q8WhfIX7tNxSwXUvAIw13hoyclajL7KIdBAKJZnlhoN4PBrmMPzwSHXDStY7_emobQA2RlrsAXCkqjv68y5z8mFBRkn0h6E1vhGey_ikoc0j3sIcB9O2PnqIngIbs08ZYwKiSeNAWlbbcuSI3AqxQidGjCO-wVjJYHhhbr03lJqoIYH-6PQu3eJUG6iuXfaN1iH-eZzAbU5tNN16QDNOy3jnKFEtQWWRhDv_RU1_IdDgn-HhjSX4Gk5xoNT95Qf_YnLgzEvav5rNfwvPaMvqbVxTHN-B74JyT0lW4HYgXzOX8G9frbh3X-bCimUyipCE