[assistant] Fixed the failing test by removing the context refresh from the package-loading helper.
[assistant] 
[assistant] Updated:
[assistant] 
[assistant] `tests/src/org.springframework.boot/spring-boot/4.0.2/src/test/java/org_springframework_boot/spring_boot/BeanDefinitionLoaderTest.java`
[assistant] 
[assistant] Change:
[assistant] 
[assistant] ```java
[assistant] application.loadSources(context, packageName);
[assistant] return context;
[assistant] ```
[assistant] 
[assistant] instead of:
[assistant] 
[assistant] ```java
[assistant] application.loadSources(context, packageName);
[assistant] context.refresh();
[assistant] return context;
[assistant] ```
[assistant] 
[assistant] Why:
[assistant] 
[assistant] - The target coverage only needs `BeanDefinitionLoader.load(...)` to resolve the package name and reach `findPackage(...)`.
[assistant] - Refreshing the context instantiates scanned Spring Boot classes as beans, which is not required and caused an unsupported bean construction failure for `CommonStructuredLogFormat`.
[assistant] - The test now verifies the package was defined after loading without triggering bean instantiation.
[assistant] 
